text: Bannock County is a county in the U.S. state of Idaho. As of the 2020 census, 87,018 people lived there, making it the sixth-most populous county in Idaho. The county seat and largest city is Pocatello. == Communities == === Cities === *Arimo *Chubbuck *Downey *Inkom *Lava Hot Springs *McCammon *Pocatello (partially in Power County) === Census-designated places === *Fort Hall (part) *Tyhee === Unincorporated communities === *Swanlake *Virginia *Robin == References == Category:1890s establishments in Idaho Category:1893 establishments in the United States Category:Idaho counties
